# SmartThinking Migration Project Goal

## Primary Objective

Modernize the SmartThinking website by migrating from the existing HTML version (located in `html-version/`) to a modern Next.js 15 application with Prismic CMS integration, while preserving the luxury aesthetic and smooth animations.

## Migration Strategy

### Phase 1: HTML Structure Extraction

- **Copy raw HTML** directly from `html-version/index.html` into React components
- **No modifications** to the original HTML structure during initial extraction
- **Preserve all** existing CSS classes, IDs, and HTML attributes
- **Convert only** HTML syntax to JSX (self-closing tags, className, etc.)
- **Create static components** first with placeholder content for development

### Phase 2: Prismic Integration (Document-Based, No Slices)

- **Homepage Document Type**: All content in single document type
- **Field-by-Field Mapping**: Map each content piece to specific Prismic fields
- **Dual Component Strategy**: Create both static and Prismic versions
- **TypeScript Integration**: Use `Content.HomepageDocumentData` types
- **Content Model Design**: Text, Image, StructuredText, and Group fields

### Phase 3: Modern Tech Stack Integration

- **Next.js 15** with App Router architecture
- **React 19** with Server Components as default
- **Prismic CMS** for content management with document-based architecture
- **GSAP Professional** for animations via Script components in layout
- **Zustand** for state management
- **TypeScript** for type safety
- **SCSS/Sass** for styling

## Key Principles & Patterns

### 1. Unified Prismic Component Architecture

- **Primary Component**: `section-name.tsx` with Prismic integration as default
- **TypeScript Integration**: Interface with `Content.HomepageDocumentData`
- **Conditional Rendering**: Graceful fallbacks when fields are empty
- **Export Pattern**: Export components from `index.ts` for clean imports

### 2. File Naming Conventions

- **Component Files**: kebab-case (`hero-section.tsx`, `work-section.tsx`)
- **Component Exports**: PascalCase (`export default HeroSection`)
- **Assets**: kebab-case with proper extensions

### 3. Content Strategy

- **Placeholder First**: Use placeholder images during development
- **Content Mapping**: Map every text/image to specific Prismic field
- **Document-Based**: No slices - everything in main homepage document
- **Field Types**: Text, StructuredText, Image, Group (repeatable)

### 4. Image Path Standards

- **Development**: Placeholder URLs (`https://placehold.co/1920x1080/333/fff`)
- **Production**: `/img/...` format in public directory
- **Prismic**: Use `PrismicNextImage` with field mapping

### 5. HTML-First Approach

- **Extract HTML structure** before adding React functionality
- **No premature optimization** with React features
- **Preserve original behavior** until explicitly modified
- **Test static version** before building Prismic version

### 6. Script Integration Pattern

- **Layout-Based**: Add all JavaScript via Next.js Script components
- **Loading Strategy**: `beforeInteractive` for critical, `afterInteractive` for others
- **File Location**: Copy all JS files to `public/js/` directory

### 7. TypeScript Integration

- **Prismic Types**: Use `Content.HomepageDocumentData` for type safety
- **Field Validation**: Use `isFilled` helpers from `@prismicio/client`
- **Component Props**: Proper interface definitions for all props

### 8. Prismic Component Patterns

- **Conditional Rendering**: Always check field existence with `data.field_name && (...)`
- **Image Components**: `PrismicNextImage` requires NO alt attribute (handled automatically)
- **Link Components**: Use `PrismicNextLink` with `field` prop for proper routing
- **Rich Text**: Use `PrismicRichText` with custom `components` for formatting control
- **Rich Text for Titles**: When using rich text for headings/titles, wrap in main component and use paragraph/strong/italic as child spans
- **Content Relationships**: Access nested data via `workItem.data.field_name`
- **Validation**: Use `isFilled.contentRelationship()` for content relationship validation
- **Key Generation**: Use meaningful keys combining index and field data
- **Dynamic Content**: Handle dynamic values like current year in component logic

### 9. Data Fetching & Performance

- **FetchLinks**: Use `fetchLinks` to include related document fields in queries
- **Field Selection**: Specify exact fields needed: `["work.title", "work.featured_image"]`
- **Content Relationships**: Configure with specific field requirements in content model
- **Query Optimization**: Apply fetchLinks to both `generateMetadata` and page functions

### 10. Animation Preservation

- **Maintain all** existing GSAP animations and effects
- **Preserve timing** and easing from original implementation
- **Keep canvas animations** (equalizer, strings, etc.)
- **Script-based loading** until NPM migration

## Success Criteria

1. ✅ **Visual Fidelity**: New site matches original design 100%
2. ✅ **Animation Quality**: All GSAP effects work smoothly
3. ✅ **Performance**: Lighthouse scores > 90 across all metrics
4. ✅ **Content Management**: Easy editing through Prismic CMS
5. ✅ **Code Quality**: Clean, maintainable, well-documented code
6. ✅ **Responsive Design**: Perfect experience across all devices

## Established Workflow Pattern

### 1. Section Analysis

- Identify HTML boundaries in `html-version/index.html`
- Note any special animations or canvas elements
- Map content that should be dynamic vs. static

### 2. Static Component Creation

```tsx
// section-name.tsx
export default function SectionName() {
  return (
    // Raw HTML converted to JSX with placeholders
  );
}
```

### 3. Prismic Content Model

```json
// Add fields to customtypes/homepage/index.json
"section_field": {
  "type": "Text|Image|StructuredText|Group",
  "config": { ... }
},
// Rich text for titles with inline formatting
"section_title": {
  "type": "StructuredText",
  "config": {
    "label": "Section Title",
    "placeholder": "Think **Beyond** The Brief",
    "allowTargetBlank": false,
    "single": "strong,paragraph,em"
  }
},
// Content relationships with specific field fetching
"related_items": {
  "type": "Group",
  "config": {
    "label": "Related Items",
    "repeat": true,
    "fields": {
      "work_item": {
        "type": "Link",
        "config": {
          "label": "Work Item",
          "select": "document",
          "customtypes": [
            {
              "id": "work",
              "fields": ["title", "featured_image"]
            }
          ]
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### 4. Prismic Component Creation

```tsx
// section-name.tsx
import { type Content, isFilled } from "@prismicio/client";
import { PrismicNextImage, PrismicNextLink } from "@prismicio/next";
import { PrismicRichText } from "@prismicio/react";

interface SectionProps {
  data: Content.HomepageDocumentData;
}

export default function SectionName({ data }: SectionProps) {
  return (
    <section>
      {/* Conditional rendering with field validation */}
      {data.section_title && <h2>{data.section_title}</h2>}

      {/* Images (no alt attribute needed) */}
      <PrismicNextImage field={data.section_image} />

      {/* Rich text with custom components */}
      <PrismicRichText
        field={data.section_content}
        components={{
          paragraph: ({ children }) => (
            <p className="custom-style">{children}</p>
          ),
        }}
      />

      {/* Rich text for titles - wrap in main component */}
      <h2 className="f-60">
        <PrismicRichText
          field={data.section_title}
          components={{
            paragraph: ({ children }) => <span>{children}</span>,
            strong: ({ children }) => <span className="Brown">{children}</span>,
            em: ({ children }) => <span className="italic">{children}</span>,
          }}
        />
      </h2>

      {/* Content relationships with validation */}
      {data.related_items?.map((item, index) => {
        const relatedItem = item.work_item;

        if (!isFilled.contentRelationship(relatedItem) || !relatedItem.data) {
          return null;
        }

        return (
          <article key={`item-${index}-${relatedItem.data.title}`}>
            <PrismicNextLink field={relatedItem}>
              <PrismicNextImage field={relatedItem.data.featured_image} />
              <h3>{relatedItem.data.title}</h3>
            </PrismicNextLink>
          </article>
        );
      })}
    </section>
  );
}
```

### 5. Testing & Integration

- Test static component first
- Test Prismic component with CMS data
- Verify animations work with JavaScript files
- Add to homepage assembly

Follow the established patterns in @general.mdc for all development work.

### Warning: Linting errors for Prismic.

- When you encounter linting errors for Prismic, just ask the user to reload the schema for you. Do not fix the linting errors yourself.
